            <head xml:id="yyy8Uu-xd6159-Hd1e103">Caput 60</head>
            <p xml:id="yyy8Uu-xd6159-d1e106">
               <lb ed="#H" n="131"/>CAPUT LX. 
      <lb ed="#H" n="132"/>In quo de observantia.
    </p>
            <p xml:id="yyy8Uu-xd6159-d1e113">
               <lb ed="#H" n="133"/>BSERVANTIA, θεργσια est virtus per quam homines 
      ve<lb ed="#H" n="134" break="no"/>Daetate vel statu vel officio, vel donis quibus a Deo ornati 
      <lb ed="#H" n="135"/>sunt, nobis superiores debito honore prosequimur &amp; colis 
      <lb ed="#H" n="136"/>Idque credendo eis sermonis, sedis, actionisque omnis primatu, 
      <lb ed="#H" n="137"/>vel gestibus idoneis pro ratione personarum, locorum &amp; temporum 
      <lb ed="#H" n="138"/>vel reverenter eos alloquendo, ut David fecit erga Saulem quam: 
      <lb ed="#H" n="139"/>vis hostem, 1. Sam. 24. 
    </p>
            <p xml:id="yyy8Uu-xd6159-d1e131">
               <lb ed="#H" n="140"/>
               <pc type="indent"/>Virtus haec exercenda: 
      <lb ed="#H" n="141"/>I. Quia divinitus est mandata, Rom. 12. v. 10. Honore alii aliis 
      <lb ed="#H" n="142"/>raeeuntes. Et cap. 13. v. 7. Reddite omnibus quod debetis, &amp;c. cui honos 
      <lb ed="#H" n="143"/>debetur, honorem. 
    </p>
            <p xml:id="yyy8Uu-xd6159-d1e144">
               <lb ed="#H" n="144"/>
               <pc type="indent"/>II. Quia favorem conciliat apud alios, ut ostendit exemplum 
      Ja<lb ed="#H" n="145" break="no"/>cobi Patriarchae, qui observantia sua Esavi favorem sibi demeruit,  
      <lb ed="#H" n="146"/>Gen. 33 
    </p>
            <p xml:id="yyy8Uu-xd6159-d1e156">
               <lb ed="#H" n="147"/>
               <pc type="indent"/>III. Quia eam suo exemplo commendant fideles, ut Abrahamus 
      <lb ed="#H" n="148"/>Gen. 23. v. 7. 
    </p>
         </div>
